22 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
23 That Section(s) 8–503 through 8–505 of Article – Election Law of the Annotated Code of
24 Maryland be repealed.
25 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
26 as follows:
27 Article – Election Law
28 1–101.
29 (a) In this article the following words have the meanings indicated unless a
30 different meaning is clearly intended from the context.
31 (II–2) “PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR” MEANS AN ELECTOR FOR PRESIDENT AND
32 VICE PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES.
33 (TT–1) “UNAFFILIATED PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE” MEANS A
34 CANDIDATE FOR PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES WHO QUALIFIES FOR THE

