4 HOUSE BILL 182
1 8–504.
2 (A) EACH PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR NOMINEE AND ALTERNATE
3 PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR NOMINEE OF A POLITICAL PARTY SHALL EXECUTE THE
4 FOLLOWING PLEDGE: “IF SELECTED FOR THE POSITION OF PRESIDENTIAL
5 ELECTOR, I AGREE TO SERVE AND TO MARK MY BALLOTS FOR PRESIDENT AND VICE
6 PRESIDENT FOR THE NOMINEES FOR THOSE OFFICES OF THE PARTY THAT
7 NOMINATED ME.”.
8 (B) EACH PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR NOMINEE AND ALTERNATE
9 PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR NOMINEE OF AN UNAFFILIATED PRESIDENTIAL
10 CANDIDATE SHALL EXECUTE THE FOLLOWING PLEDGE: “IF SELECTED FOR THE
11 POSITION OF PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR AS A NOMINEE OF AN UNAFFILIATED
12 PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE, I AGREE TO SERVE AND TO MARK MY BALLOTS FOR THAT
13 CANDIDATE AND FOR THAT CANDIDATE’S VICE PRESIDENTIAL RUNNING MATE.”.
14 (C) THE EXECUTED PLEDGES SHALL ACCOMPANY THE SUBMISSION OF THE
15 CORRESPONDING PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR NOMINEE NAMES TO THE STATE BOARD.
16 (D) IF, AFTER THE NOMINATION OF A CANDIDATE FOR PRESIDENT OR VICE
17 PRESIDENT BY A POLITICAL PARTY AND BEFORE THE MEETING OF PRESIDENTIAL
18 ELECTORS UNDER § 8–508 OF THIS SUBTITLE, THE CANDIDATE DIES OR WITHDRAWS
19 AS A CANDIDATE FOR THAT OFFICE IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE RULES OF THE
20 POLITICAL PARTY, THE PLEDGE EXECUTED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
21 SECTION OR § 8–507(D) OF THIS SUBTITLE APPLIES TO THE SUCCESSOR CANDIDATE
22 FOR THAT OFFICE NOMINATED BY THE POLITICAL PARTY IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE
23 PARTY RULES.
24 [8–504.] 8–505.
25 (a) (1) At the general election for President and Vice President of the United
26 States there shall be elected, in accordance with subsection (b) of this section, the number
27 of presidential electors to which this State is entitled.
28 (2) Presidential electors shall be elected:
29 (I) IF § 8–5A–01 OF THIS TITLE IS NOT IN EFFECT, AT LARGE BY
30 THE VOTERS OF THE ENTIRE STATE; OR
31 (II) IF § 8–5A–01 OF THIS TITLE IS IN EFFECT, under the
32 procedure provided in § 8–5A–01 of this title.

