29 (B) THE POSITION OF A PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR NOT PRESENT TO VOTE IS
30 VACANT.
31 (C) THE STATE ADMINISTRATOR PRESIDENTIAL ELECTORS STILL SERVING
32 SHALL APPOINT AN INDIVIDUAL AS A SUBSTITUTE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR TO FILL
33 A VACANCY AS FOLLOWS:

6 HOUSE BILL 182
1 (1) IF THE ALTERNATE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR IS PRESENT TO
2 VOTE, BY APPOINTING THE ALTERNATE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR FOR THE VACANT
3 POSITION;
4 (2) IF THE ALTERNATE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR FOR THE VACANT
5 POSITION IS NOT PRESENT TO VOTE, BY APPOINTING A PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR
6 CHOSEN BY LOT FROM AMONG THE ALTERNATE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTORS PRESENT
7 TO VOTE WHO WERE NOMINATED BY THE SAME POLITICAL PARTY OR THE
8 UNAFFILIATED PRESIDENTIAL CANDIDATE;
9 (3) IF THE NUMBER OF ALTERNATE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTORS
10 PRESENT TO VOTE IS INSUFFICIENT TO FILL ANY VACANT POSITION IN ACCORDANCE
11 WITH ITEM (1) OR (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, BY APPOINTING ANY IMMEDIATELY
12 AVAILABLE INDIVIDUAL WHO IS QUALIFIED TO SERVE AS A PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR
13 AND CHOSEN THROUGH NOMINATION BY AND PLURALITY VOTE OF THE REMAINING
14 PRESIDENTIAL ELECTORS, INCLUDING NOMINATION AND VOTE BY A SINGLE
15 PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR IF ONLY ONE REMAINS;
16 (4) IF THERE IS A TIE BETWEEN AT LEAST TWO NOMINEES FOR
17 SUBSTITUTE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR IN A VOTE CONDUCTED UNDER ITEM (3) OF
18 THIS SUBSECTION, BY APPOINTING A PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR CHOSEN BY LOT
19 FROM AMONG THOSE NOMINEES; OR
20 (5) IF ALL PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR POSITIONS ARE VACANT AND
21 CANNOT BE FILLED IN ACCORDANCE WITH ITEM (1), (2), (3), OR (4) OF THIS
22 SUBSECTION, BY APPOINTING A SINGLE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR, WITH REMAINING
23 VACANT POSITIONS TO BE FILLED IN ACCORDANCE WITH ITEM (3) OR (4) OF THIS
24 SUBSECTION.
25 (D) TO QUALIFY AS A SUBSTITUTE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR UNDER
26 SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, AN INDIVIDUAL WHO HAS NOT EXECUTED THE
27 PLEDGE REQUIRED UNDER § 8–504 OF THIS SUBTITLE SHALL EXECUTE THE
28 FOLLOWING PLEDGE: “I AGREE TO SERVE AND TO MARK MY BALLOTS FOR
29 PRESIDENT AND VICE PRESIDENT CONSISTENT WITH THE PLEDGE OF THE
30 INDIVIDUAL TO WHOSE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR POSITION I HAVE SUCCEEDED.”.
31 [8–505.] 8–508.
32 (a) (1) The individuals elected to the office of presidential elector shall meet in
33 the State House in the City of Annapolis on the day provided by the Constitution and laws
34 of the United States.
35 (2) The conduct of the meeting shall be consistent with the requirements
36 of federal law.

