10 VOTES ARE CONSISTENT WITH THEIR PLEDGES EXECUTED FOR THE CANDIDATES
11 FOR PRESIDENT AND VICE PRESIDENT WHO ARE THE NATIONAL POPULAR VOTE
12 WINNERS AS DEFINED IN § 8–5A–01 OF THIS TITLE.
13 (2) THE STATE ADMINISTRATOR MAY NOT COUNT EITHER A
14 PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR’S PRESIDENTIAL OR VICE PRESIDENTIAL BALLOT IF THE
15 PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR HAS NOT MARKED BOTH BALLOTS OR HAS MARKED A
16 BALLOT IN VIOLATION OF THE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR’S PLEDGE.
17 (E) A PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR WHO REFUSES TO PRESENT A BALLOT,
18 PRESENTS AN UNMARKED BALLOT, OR PRESENTS A BALLOT MARKED IN VIOLATION
19 OF THE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR’S PLEDGE EXECUTED UNDER § 8–504 OR § 8–507(D)
20 OF THIS SUBTITLE VACATES THE OFFICE OF ELECTOR, CREATING A VACANT
21 POSITION TO BE FILLED UNDER § 8–507 OF THIS SUBTITLE.
22 (F) THE STATE ADMINISTRATOR SHALL DISTRIBUTE BALLOTS AND
23 COLLECT BALLOTS FROM A SUBSTITUTE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTOR AND REPEAT THE
24 PROCESS UNDER THIS SECTION, DECLARING AND FILLING VACANT POSITIONS AS
25 REQUIRED, AND RECORDING APPROPRIATELY COMPLETED BALLOTS FROM THE
26 SUBSTITUTE PRESIDENTIAL ELECTORS, UNTIL ALL OF THIS STATE’S ELECTORAL
27 VOTES HAVE BEEN CAST AND RECORDED.
28 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Section 2 of this Act shall take
29 effect October 1, 2026. It shall remain effective until the taking effect of Section 1 of
30 Chapters 43 and 44 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2007. If the contingency stated
31 in Section 3 of Chapters 43 and 44 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2007 takes effect,
32 Section 2 of this Act shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
33 SECTION 5. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Section 3 of this Act shall take
34 effect on the taking effect of Section 1 of Chapters 43 and 44 of the Acts of the General
35 Assembly of 2007.

14 HOUSE BILL 182
1 SECTION 6. 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, subject to the provisions
2 of Sections 4 and 5 of this Act, this Act shall take effect October 1, 2026.
Approved:
